definition.value: A member of the class of  pyrazolidines that is 1,2-diphenylpyrazolidine-3,5-dione carrying a butyl group at the 4-position.
An indol-3-ylacetaldehyde oxime in which the oxime moiety has Z configuration.
A role played by a substance that can react readily with, and thereby eliminate, radicals.

A triazolo[4,3-a][1,4]benzodiazepine having a phenyl group at position 6 and a chloro substituent at position 8. A short-acting benzodiazepine with general properties similar to diazepam, it is given by mouth as a hypnotic in the short-term management of insomnia.
A 5'-deoxyribonucleoside consisting of inosine where the 5'-hydroxy group is substituted by a methylsulfanyl group.
An arsenate ion resulting from the removal of two protons from arsenic acid.
An arsenate ion resulting from the removal of one proton from arsenic acid.
A metal chloride salt with a Li(+) counterion.
A dimethylnaphthalene carrying methyl groups at positions 1 and 4.
A dimethylnaphthalene carrying methyl groups at positions 1 and 7.
A dimethylnaphthalene carrying methyl groups at positions 1 and 3.
A dimethylnaphthalene carrying methyl groups at positions 2 and 3.
